quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
26,207,"of what avail will be the provisions of life which they have been granted to enjoy? {1}",footnotes:1:That is
26,208,"We never destroyed any habitation but that it had warners"
26,209,"to admonish them. We have never been unjust. {1}",footnotes:1:After the positive aspect as stated in (verses 192-193)
26,210,"The satans {1} did not bring down this (Clear Book),",footnotes:1:That is
26,211,"nor does it behove them, {1} nor does it lie in their power. {2}",footnotes:1:Tell them: if what you say be true
26,212,"Indeed they are debarred from even hearing it. {1}",footnotes:1:This does not mean that the Prophet (peace be upon him) was going to be involved in shirk from which he was to be admonished to desist. The object was to warn the disbelievers and polytheists to the effect: As the message of the Quran is based on pure truth revealed by the Almighty Ruler of the universe
26,213,"So do not call any other god beside Allah lest you become of those who will be punished, {1}",footnotes:1:Just as there could be no concession or favor for the person of the Prophet (peace be upon him) in a matter concerning Allah’s religion
26,214,"and warn your nearest kinsmen; {1}",footnotes:1:This can have two meanings.
26,215,"and be meek to the believers who follow you."
26,216,"Then if they disobey you say to them: "I am quit of what you do." {1}",footnotes:1:That is
26,217,"And put your trust in Him Who is Immensely Mighty, Most Compassionate, {1}",footnotes:1:“Stand up” may mean getting up for the Prayers during the night
26,218,"Who observes you when you rise (to pray) {1}",footnotes:1:This can have several meanings.
26,219,"and observes your movements among those who prostrate themselves. {1}",footnotes:1:This implies the sorcerers
26,220,"He is All-Hearing, All-Knowing."
26,221,"O people, shall I tell you on whom it is that satans descend?"
26,222,"They descend on every forgerer steeped in sin, {1}",footnotes:1:This may have two meanings. (1) The satans somehow get a little hint of the truth and inspire their agents with it
26,223,"on those who whisper hearsay in the ears of people; and most of them are liars. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
26,224,"As for poets, only the wayward follow them. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
26,225,"Do you not see that they wander about in every valley {1}",footnotes:1:This characteristic of the poets was just the antithesis of the Prophet’s (peace be upon him) conduct and practice. Everybody knew that the Prophet (peace be upon him) said what he practiced and practiced what he said. The fact that there was complete conformity between his word and deed could not be denied by anybody. On the contrary
26,226,"and say things which they do not act upon, {1}",footnotes:1:Here those poets have made an exception from the general reproach
26,227,"except those who believed and acted righteously and remembered Allah much, and when they themselves were subjected to wrong, they exacted retribution no more than to the extent of the wrong? {1} Soon will the wrong-doers know the end that they shall reach.",footnotes:1:“Those who do wrong”: The people who out of sheer obduracy calumniated the Prophet (peace be upon him) of being a sorcerer
